Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 788 “The Mystery \NSinking in the Midsummer Pool (Part 2)”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:07.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sera Masumi invited Ran, Sonoko, and I\Nto visit her at the hotel she's living at.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.72,0:00:12.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to hang out at the pool,\Nbut the daughter of the hotel's owner,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.99,0:00:19.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Nagami-ojosama, kicked out the other\Nguests to look for the necklace she lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:17.70,Daughter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oiso Nagami (31)\NPresident's Daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.08,0:00:25.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After lunch, we returned to the pool and \Ndiscovered Nagami-ojosama was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.97,0:00:28.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.89,0:00:30.34,DCItalic,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:34.10,DCItalic,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's something in\Nthe middle of the pool!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:34.72,DCItalic,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.48,0:00:38.72,DCItalic,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,Is... Is that a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:39.47,DCItalic,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.53,0:00:47.65,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagami...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:49.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...Ojosama?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.66,0:00:56.46,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}But didn't Nagami-san say\Nher fiancé Samaki-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:00:59.41,Sister,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Oiso Hamaka (28)\NNagami's Half-Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:00:59.41,Secretary,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Samaki Raito (30)\NPresident's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.46,0:00:59.41,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}...and sister Hamaka-san were a couple?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.68,0:01:04.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She said the hotel manager was \Nletting them use the hotel to meet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.24,0:01:05.61,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I-It's a misunderstanding.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.61,0:01:07.71,DCItalic,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My sister was overthinking things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.03,0:01:12.64,DCItalic,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Her birthday was coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.64,0:01:18.84,DCItalic,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning to celebrate in the \Nsuite since she loves this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:21.72,DCItalic,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,We discussed decorations and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.76,0:01:27.10,Manager,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Toyoshima Ensaku\N(56) Hotel Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.94,0:01:27.10,DCItalic,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Since it was a surprise, we \Ndidn't tell Nagami-ojosama.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.30,0:01:33.48,DCItalic,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Because we were meeting in that room, she \Ngot the wrong idea and said those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.74,0:01:41.14,DCItalic,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She really did like that room, so \NI'm not surprised she was angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.82,0:01:42.95,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That much?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:48.50,DCItalic,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She's even kicked out guests with \Na reservation to stay in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.76,0:01:53.05,DCItalic,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,So we had no motive to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.44,0:01:56.13,DCItalic,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to celebrate her birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.13,0:01:59.88,DCItalic,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,If you doubt us, ask the hotel staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.88,0:02:04.37,DCItalic,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,We discussed the party\Ndecorations with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.13,0:02:08.27,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be confirming that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:14.57,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,First I'd like to hear what you were \Ndoing after you left Nagami-san alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:22.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Propelled forward by the \Nyears spent together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.93,0:02:25.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Charging full speed ahead \Nwithout slowing the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:27.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone says something odd by the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.42,0:02:29.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The truth comes rising to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:32.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.67,0:02:34.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.98,0:04:19.98,DCEpTitle,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)|}The Mystery Sinking in the \NMidsummer Pool (Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:18.59,DCMain,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,The Mystery Sinking in the \NMidsummer Pool, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:24.49,Reception,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Reception
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:24.49,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.71,0:04:29.49,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,Only the staff entered the pool\Nafter we were ordered to close it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.79,0:04:37.14,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,The manager, Hamaka-ojosama, secretary \NSamaki-san, and those two bellboys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.14,0:04:42.42,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,Before Nagami-ojosama was left \Nalone, we let those girls through.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:45.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We forgot something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:48.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We just wanted to see what was going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:54.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,After Nagami-san said she'd search alone, \Nwho was the first to return here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:05:00.19,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it was Manager Toyoshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.69,0:05:03.86,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,He said he wanted to check on Nagami-ojosama.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.17,0:05:06.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know when that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.41,0:05:08.48,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,After 12 PM, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.81,0:05:12.86,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,She had just received an e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:15.19,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.61,0:05:17.12,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,That was 12:05.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.53,0:05:19.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What was she doing then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:22.55,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She was looking for her necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.13,0:05:26.78,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,It took her a while to notice I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:33.81,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But when she noticed, she said that \NI was in the way, so I quickly left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:35.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.47,0:05:38.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What about after the manager left?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:39.48,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.48,0:05:43.69,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,The next person was Samaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:44.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:48.07,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,She was taking a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.43,0:05:52.99,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to tell her to\Nlet someone else do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:57.63,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't see her in or near the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:02.50,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought she might be in the \Nbathroom, so I waited by the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:07.01,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,She showed no signs of returning, so I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:09.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know when you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.93,0:06:11.07,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:13.70,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:16.00,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,We don't keep notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:23.68,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,But Hamaka-ojosama, who arrived \Nwhen he left, left at 12:54.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.68,0:06:27.15,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,She asked us the time as she was leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.51,0:06:29.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.29,0:06:33.62,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I had a 1 PM reservation \Nfor lunch at this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:39.16,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Samaki-san asked me to check \Nthe bathroom and changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:42.17,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't in either, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:46.26,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't at the pool, \Neither, so I panicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.26,0:06:51.76,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't trust my phone's clock, \Nso I asked to check the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.76,0:06:54.93,DCMain,TAKAGAI,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where are the \Nbathroom and changing room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:06:56.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.01,0:07:01.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The changing room and showers are \Nbetween reception and the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.43,0:07:03.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The bathroom's back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:08.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You could hide a body here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.08,0:07:13.07,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The two receptionists \Ncan't see back here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:15.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What happened next?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.26,0:07:19.21,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,We called the manager and Samaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.21,0:07:23.27,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,We called the bellboys, too, and \Nthey split up to look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:25.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where was Nagami-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:28.90,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:31.90,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,We searched showers and lockers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.90,0:07:36.51,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We even searched the men's \Nrooms while calling for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.13,0:07:40.07,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't find her after \Nan hour of searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.07,0:07:45.93,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,so we asked the receptionists if \Nthey really didn't see her leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.93,0:07:47.55,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when they came.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:54.58,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,While we were explaining the situation, \Nthe bellboys saw her body in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.58,0:07:55.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.32,0:08:00.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By why did you come back to search the pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:03.38,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't there when you \Nlooked together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:06.60,DCMain,BOY A,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I had a bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.60,0:08:10.81,DCMain,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I heard a strange \Nnoise coming from the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:13.68,DCMain,BOY B,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like some big bubbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.48,0:08:26.71,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.71,0:08:28.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The drain's grate is screwed in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.38,0:08:30.73,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.22,0:08:35.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There's a hook stuck in the \Nwall directly above the drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.82,0:08:39.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the exact center \Nof the pool wall, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:42.46,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.46,0:08:44.12,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.59,0:08:46.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:51.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In summary,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.68,0:08:57.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the victim Oiso Nagami-san said she'd search \Nfor the necklace she lost at the pool alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.74,0:09:03.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,After kicking the three of you out, at 12:05,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.35,0:09:08.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the manager Toyoshima-san \Ncame to check on Nagami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.68,0:09:10.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She said he was in the \Nway and made him leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.94,0:09:16.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Next, when the secretary Samaki-san came, \Nhe didn't see Nagami-san in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.63,0:09:20.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hamaka-san arrived as Samaki-san left,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:24.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and he told her to check the \Nchanging room and bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:29.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She confirmed she wasn't there at 12:54.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.64,0:09:38.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Later, the three of you and the two bellboys \Nsplit up to search but couldn't find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.64,0:09:40.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Ten minutes after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.55,0:09:47.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the two bellboys returned to the pool \Nand found Nagami-san in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.29,0:09:51.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are those the correct times \Nand sequence of events?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.34,0:09:52.58,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST A,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:54.36,DCMain,RECEPTIONIST B,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.36,0:09:59.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Nagami-san died between noon and 1 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.77,0:10:04.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,During that time, only you three \Nentered and left the pool area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.42,0:10:08.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,One of you must have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.83,0:10:12.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if the body was in \Nthe pool the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.42,0:10:16.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,then someone would have found \Nit while you split up to search.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:22.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, it's hard to \Nimagine someone put the body
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:27.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,in the middle of the pool unnoticed \Nwhile you were searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.34,0:10:30.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is an impossible crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:32.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Takagi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.53,0:10:34.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:37.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Takagi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.84,0:10:44.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi headed to the pool \Nafter talking to Conan-kun and Sera-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.63,0:10:46.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.61,0:10:50.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,While you were in the bathroom, he \Nwas carrying around a big aquarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:52.63,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He said it was for an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:55.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:10:59.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not Sera-san. Sera-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:01.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.41,0:11:05.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Also, he said we should all \Ncome see the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.13,0:11:08.48,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it will expose the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.52,0:11:20.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Takagi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:25.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:29.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And why is there water in the pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:33.75,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,We finished investigating, so we thought \Nwe'd try Takagi-san's experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:36.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.32,0:11:38.37,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:41.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:44.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're up to, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:46.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Takagi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:49.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Come out and explain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.58,0:11:52.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.78,0:11:53.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.92,0:11:56.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:58.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.46,0:11:59.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:00.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:01.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.41,0:12:06.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.80,0:12:08.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.39,0:12:10.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see him, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.29,0:12:12.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see him right now, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.65,0:12:17.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if you cut the fishing \Nline attached to this hook...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:22.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A-An aquarium?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.60,0:12:27.22,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,D-Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.44,0:12:30.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:33.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,No, but why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.81,0:12:35.48,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Because the light was reflected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.66,0:12:36.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:42.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Both water and air are clear, but water \Nhas a different refractive index.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:48.24,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When light passes from the highly refractive \Nwater to the less refractive air,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:53.06,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,if you look at the boundary between \Nthe water and air head on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:13:00.12,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,all the light is reflected like a mirror, \Nand you can't see objects on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.43,0:13:03.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:12.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can see my ten yen coin \Ninside the aquarium, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.53,0:13:14.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:20.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if you turn a cup upside down and put \Nit over the coin while there's air inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:23.28,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,I-It disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.48,0:13:25.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:27.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a science experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.51,0:13:30.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You probably learned \Nabout it in grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.07,0:13:32.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.84,0:13:36.89,DCItalic,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They teach this complicated stuff \Nto first year grade school students?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:39.46,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi used the same trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.82,0:13:43.50,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Because he was inside an upside \Ndown aquarium filled with air,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.50,0:13:46.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,we couldn't see him in the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.53,0:13:48.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:51.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But couldn't you see him from directly above?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.28,0:13:53.31,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:58.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you view the boundary between \Nthe air and water at a low angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.14,0:14:00.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't reflect the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.37,0:14:01.98,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But this is a pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.98,0:14:04.32,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You can't look from directly above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.77,0:14:06.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.54,0:14:12.49,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,After drowning Nagami-san, who was \Nsearching for her necklace alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.98,0:14:17.62,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit placed an aquarium \Nover her body and secured it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.18,0:14:24.22,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,using a fishing line passed through \Nthe drains on both sides of the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.02,0:14:29.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Then they tilted the aquarium, \Nslipped their hand in,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:35.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and released the air from Nagami-san's \Ntank to fill the aquarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.60,0:14:42.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Fishing line is elastic, so it could \Nhandle the aquarium being tilted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.89,0:14:47.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But how did they drown her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.46,0:14:48.99,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It was simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.99,0:14:53.03,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,They said something to her so \Nshe would let her guard down,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.43,0:15:00.29,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,grabbed her neck from behind, removed \Nher mouthpiece, and held her under.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.89,0:15:04.61,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,With the tank and weights, \NNagami-san sank easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.61,0:15:07.84,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,No one could hear her scream underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.51,0:15:13.30,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, hotel manager Toyoshima Ensaku-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.90,0:15:19.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you lower her guard \Nby pointing at the pool
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.02,0:15:26.44,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,by your feet and saying \Nher necklace was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:31.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But can you really secure an aquarium \Nwith a single fishing line?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.84,0:15:34.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it full of air?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you make four grooves and set the \Nline in them, it won't float easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:49.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And if you attach the end of the line to a \Nhook attached near the surface of the pool,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:58.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,even if you're not in the water, you can cut the \Nline, make the aquarium float, and reveal the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:01.21,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Conan-kun did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:09.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Toyoshima-san drowned Nagami-san \Nwhen he came to check on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:13.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,sank her body and hid it using \Nthe trick we just described.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.22,0:16:20.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When everyone finished searching, he \Ncut the line, and revealed the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:25.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the aquarium made a pretty \Nbig noise when it floated up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.06,0:16:29.59,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He shouted something as he was doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:33.59,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Like, “Where are you, Nagami-ojosama?”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.15,0:16:38.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else looking for \Nher was shouting, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.27,0:16:40.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The sound was barely audible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.40,0:16:44.16,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But the aquarium was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.16,0:16:49.27,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not in the middle of the pool \Nnear her body, but by the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.49,0:16:52.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, when did he move it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.04,0:16:57.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It had to have been when they pulled \NNagami-san's body out of the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.83,0:17:02.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the only thing the manager \Nwas carrying was the tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.54,0:17:08.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he stuck his foot in the aquarium \Nand dragged it along the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:09.52,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:15.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After bringing it to the edge, he struck \Nit with the tank and shattered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.53,0:17:19.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else was watching her body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.72,0:17:22.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and it would have been barely \Naudible in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.93,0:17:28.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the manager hurt himself \Non the broken glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:30.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Would he have done that on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:32.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.76,0:17:37.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No one would think the man who \Nhurt himself would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.50,0:17:41.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if the police were going\Nto find the aquarium anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:46.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd smash it so they wouldn't know its shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:48.54,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a tricky little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:50.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You won't grow up into a moral adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.25,0:17:55.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was just imagining if I had done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:57.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really the problem here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.13,0:18:01.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:03.06,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:10.81,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When he cut it, he had to quickly reel in the\Nline attached to the drain on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.24,0:18:16.19,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Manager Toyoshima's fingerprints \Nshould be all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.73,0:18:20.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't fishing line really thin?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.29,0:18:21.62,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe individual lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.09,0:18:25.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But he probably gathered it \Ntogether while reeling them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:30.17,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,so his fingerprints should \Nmatch up to a few places.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.66,0:18:33.89,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You can find that, right, forensics?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:34.96,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:39.54,DCMain,SAMAKI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But he had no motive to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:40.68,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.68,0:18:45.39,DCMain,HAMAKA,0000,0000,0000,,We discussed celebrating \Nher birthday together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.00,0:18:51.15,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to celebrate, \Nespecially not in that suite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:52.17,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:56.12,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I had a much younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.12,0:19:03.78,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She reserved the room with her husband \Nbecause they wanted just once to stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:08.52,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,They were celebrating their \Nson's third birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.43,0:19:11.52,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,The room has a good view,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.52,0:19:15.91,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,and that day's fireworks display would \Nhave been visible from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.26,0:19:18.94,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.94,0:19:24.43,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Nagami-ojosama said she wanted to view the \Nfireworks from that room with her friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.79,0:19:29.07,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,My sister's family had to\Nmove to another hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.07,0:19:34.19,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,On the way there, they got in \Nan accident, and they all died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.85,0:19:36.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:40.19,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So you resented her for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.47,0:19:43.52,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,For that? Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:48.33,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,That day, she didn't stay in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:50.86,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:57.67,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Because her friend's car she was taking \Nto the hotel caused an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.02,0:20:04.36,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That woman was riding in the \Ncar that killed my sister's family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:13.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But how did you find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.11,0:20:18.27,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She called me that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.81,0:20:22.65,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She was riding in her friend's \Ncar when it caused an accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.65,0:20:24.28,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,but she didn't want to get involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.83,0:20:31.29,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,She asked me to pretend she had been \Nin the suite since that afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.07,0:20:36.57,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, I'd been waiting \Nfor my opportunity for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:40.30,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,For her to come to this pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.85,0:20:47.80,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Removing the necklace that would \Nset my plan in motion was a gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.85,0:20:52.18,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,But heaven was on my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.56,0:21:00.50,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, though, those young detectives \Nexposed the murder I planned so carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.50,0:21:04.26,DCMain,TOYOSHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,It was all for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.38,0:22:31.59,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.59,0:22:35.79,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You came to see me, but \NI wasn't much of a host.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.02,0:22:38.57,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't help it. There was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.57,0:22:44.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like what happened \Nat the “Which Sweets SHOW.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.47,0:22:48.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You make people appear and \Ndisappear out of thin air.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.37,0:22:50.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're like a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.61,0:22:52.13,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,A magician?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.20,0:22:55.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.83,0:22:56.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.53,0:23:01.92,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You're a magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.11,0:23:08.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,L-Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.69,0:23:12.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sera-chan, have we met before?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.86,0:23:15.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You just said Sera-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.25,0:23:16.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.58,0:23:18.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You can call me Sera-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.87,0:23:20.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,She says it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:21.94,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
